Host Russia is currently 2-0 up against Saudi Arabia in the opening match of the 2018 FIFA World Cup. Yuri Gazinskiy  scored the first goal of the 2018 FIFA World Cup after 12’minutes, with Denis Cheryshev getting  the second in 43’minutes Earlier, Russian president Vladimir Putin  gave a speech at the Luzhniki Stadium, welcoming the World to Russia. “We are sincerely happy to host the World Cup in our country,” he said. “Football is truly loved here. Russia is an open, hospitable and friendly country.”